<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Wally's Weather API</title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }
      h1 {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      h2 {
        margin-top: 30px;
      }
      p {
        margin-bottom: 15px;
      }
      code {
        background-color: #f4f4f4;
        padding: 5px;
        border-radius: 4px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Wally's Weather API</h1>
      <h2>Weather API</h2>
      <p>To retrieve weather information, send a <strong>POST</strong> request to the following endpoint:</p>
      <code>{{currentUrl}}/weather</code>
      <p>The request body should include the following parameters:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>location</strong>: The location for which you want to retrieve weather information.</li>
        <li><strong>extended</strong>: Set to <strong>hourly</strong>, <strong>daily</strong>, or <strong>weekly</strong> for different forecast intervals.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Giphy API</h2>
      <p>To retrieve a GIF based on weather conditions, send a <strong>POST</strong> request to the following endpoint:</p>
      <code>{{currentUrl}}/giphy</code>
      <p>The request body should include the following parameter:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>weather</strong>: The weather condition for which you want to retrieve a GIF.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
